**सबहि भाँति हरि ही को पूजै । राग द्वेष द्वन्दन सौं जूझै ॥**

Word-by-word breakdown:

**सबहि** (sabahi) - "in all"
**भाँति** (bhaanti) - "ways" or "manners"
**हरि** (hari) - "Hari" (name for God/Vishnu)
**ही** (hi) - "only" or "alone" (emphatic)
**को** (ko) - "to" (postposition)
**पूजै** (pujai) - "worship" or "honor"

**राग** (raga) - "attachment" or "passion"
**द्वेष** (dvesha) - "hatred" or "aversion"
**द्वन्दन** (dvandana) - "dualities" or "pairs of opposites"
**सौं** (saun) - "with" or "from"
**जूझै** (juujhai) - "fight" or "struggle"

Translation: "In all ways may I worship Hari alone, and struggle against attachment, hatred, and the confusion of dualities."